Sentencas: Nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) is investigated for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells based on SDC- 30 wt% (53 mol% Li2CO3:47 mol % Na2CO3) composite electrolyte in this work.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SDC is prepared by the combined citrate and EDTA complexing method.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: X-ray powder diffraction shows that it forms a well-cubic fluorite structure after being sintered at 700 degrees C for 2 h. The particle is about 12 nm detected by the transmission electron microscopy.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Conductivity for the composite is much higher than the pure SDC at comparable temperatures.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A transition of ionic conductivity occurs at 450 degrees C for the composite electrolyte.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The single cells are fabricated by a simple dry-pressing process and tested at 450-600 degrees C. A maximum power density of 900 mW cm(-2) and the open-circuit voltage of 0.92 V are achieved at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The conduction mechanism has been discussed by comparing the conductivity of composite electrolyte under different conditions.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: AC impedance for single cell indicates that the electrochemical process involving cathode and anode reactions is the rate-limiting step.
Titulo: Composite electrolyte based on nanostructured Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
